                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B816E">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_EscEngineLimitsManagement</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_EscEngineLimitsManagement</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This Behavior description aims at treating the different limitations requested by Bodybuilder Equipement.
The following requirements will explain how Engine Speed and Torque Limitations shall be computed and when.

This behavior delivers 1 piece of information to other behaviors in this component:
EscMinEngineSpeed
</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B66F4">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_EscConfigurationManagement</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_EscConfigurationManagement</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This Behavior description aims at defining which configuration to be applied in Engine Speed Control. The configuration to be applied is based on different information. It will be an input for other components. 

2 different strategies to choose the current configuration:
The first one is purely based on the request done by the user (Engine Speed Modes based)
The second one is based on both PTOs currently active, and selection done by the user (Pto based)

This behavior delivers 2 pieces of information to other behaviors in this component:
EscCurrentConfiguration
EscEngineSpeedSelection
</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B2F58">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Routine_Control_Calibration_of_K_factor</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Routine_Control_Calibration_of_K_factor</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>When the K-factor calibration service is running, the number of pulses received since the service is started shall be stored, and possible to read out.

Note:
The K-factor calibration service shall follow the ISO 14229 standard for RoutineControl service.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BE08C">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Calculate_and_distribute_vehicle_speed</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Calculate_and_distribute_vehicle_speed</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This Logical Design Component is responsible for calculating and distributing the vehicle speed based on information from the Tachograph and the speed pulse sensor.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BE09A">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Initiate_synchronize_and_distribute_the_K_factor</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Initiate_synchronize_and_distribute_the_K_factor</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This Logical Design Component is responsible for K-factor management. The K-factor can be set in three different ways; either from the Tachograph, from last known K-factor received from the Tachograph or from a parameter.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BE093">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Calculate_and_distribute_output_shaft_speed</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Calculate_and_distribute_output_shaft_speed</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This Logical Design Component is responsible for calculating the output shaft speed based on information from the speed pulse input period time and the number of output shaft cogs.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BA84B">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Calculate_and_distribute_vehicle_distance_rolling_counter</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Calculate_and_distribute_vehicle_distance_rolling_counter</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>nil reference shall be calculated as (n * 1000) / K-Factor, where n is the number of pulses for the distance traveled.

If nil reference is valid, the number of pulses for the distance traveled (n) shall be accumulated from nil reference.
nil reference shall wrap around when the calculated distance according to the calculation above reaches the maximum value for nil reference. 

Note: &quot;Valid&quot; is defined when the signal
a) is received 
b) contains a value which is not out of range, &quot;Error&quot; or &quot;Not available&quot;.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B6163">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Start_up_of_the_handler</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Start_up_of_the_handler</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>When this handler is going from an inactive vehicle mode to an active vehicle mode, signal PrimaryAcctrPedalPosition shall be sent out as Not available for 500 ms.

Descriptions
This will solve the problem that the sensors send out error when they start up.

</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
