                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BD7E2">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Supervise_expected_behaviour</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Supervise_expected_behaviour</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This component shall supervise that commands sent to the MainSystemSound_hdlrs and ClusterSystemSound_hdlr are carried out and that the handlers act according to expected behavior. The signals ClusterSSStat and MainSSStat shall be used for this monitoring feedback.
For a non-continuous sound: If feedback Stopped is not received, same sound shall be in hold for 10 seconds, and first after this another request of the same sound will be accepted again.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B63C0">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Stop_a_continuos_sound</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Stop_a_continuos_sound</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>For sounds with 'Repetition' is continuos in the configurable parameters for sound attributes, the following shall replace the previous command:

Parameter
Value
ID
-
State
Stop
Repetition
-
Time
-
Volume
-
Balance
-
Mixed
-
</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AF68F">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Stop_command</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Stop_command</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>When receiving a request to stop playing a specific sound the State parameter in signal is the only valid one. I.e. All other parameters may have any value.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B0ADD">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Detecting_Button_Pushes_on_Infotainment_Panel</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Detecting_Button_Pushes_on_Infotainment_Panel</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>In the HMI of the truck there are two concepts called display focus and black panel. 

The display focus concept means that one display (SID or DID) is in focus. In order to support that functionality and based on the fact that all buttons are routed via this component this component is responsible for detecting button pushes on the infotainment panel.

The black panel concept means that several of the indicator devices in the truck might be switched off in order to minimize the amount of light in the cab. This functionality relies on the button pushes on the infotainment panel.

This component shall detect any button push or wheel rotation on the infotainment panel and report that by sending WorkStInputEvStat signal as soon as a button or free wheel on the infotainment panel is pushed.

Information: This means that a button that is routed according to the button routing tables might be distributed to WorkStInputEvStat signal also.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B6C89">
                  <SHORT-NAME>DBL_status_icon_in_DID_statusbar_when_DBL_failure</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>DBL_status_icon_in_DID_statusbar_when_DBL_failure</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>When a vehicle message is displayed due to a failure in the Dynamic bending lights functionality a status icon in the DID status bar shall be displayed as well. 

For information about the Status icon look and feel see view flow 26331-596: 007.

This shall be signalled by GUIDataInterface.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B6786">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Detection_and_handling_for_stucked_buttons_Updated_Gear_stalk_</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Detection_and_handling_for_stucked_buttons_Updated_Gear_stalk_</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>If any of the input switch status signals GearShiftInputStatus, AutoManualToggleStatus, DriveNeutralInputStatus or CrawlReverseInputStatus is detected to be active in a momentary returning position for longer than a certain configurable time (nil reference ) then the input signal should be treated within this LDC as set to the value corresponding to the resting position of the input signal until the value in the input signal changes again.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B6727">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Detection_and_handling_for_stuck_buttons_Button_panel_</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Detection_and_handling_for_stuck_buttons_Button_panel_</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT></TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001ACBF8">
