                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AF37E">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Display_resource_signal_interface</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Display_resource_signal_interface</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The display resource signals to be used by this component are: &quot;XX&quot;DispResReq, &quot;XX&quot;DispResRsp and &quot;XX&quot;DispResStat where &quot;XX&quot; should be replaced by the name of the HMICtrl.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AF373">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Sending_XX_AppEvCmd</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Sending_XX_AppEvCmd</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This component should use the signal &quot;XX&quot;AppEvCmd to send event commands to the GUI. &quot;XX&quot; should be replaced by the name of the HMICtrl. 
This signal is only allowed to be used by the HMICtrl that has a DisplayMode that is granted.
The event shall always relate to the DisplayMode that is currently granted.
The signal shall be sent to the display that is allocated to the DisplayMode that is granted.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BDAA6">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_Handling_of_button_presses_Internal_HMICtrls</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_Handling_of_button_presses_Internal_HMICtrls</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This HMICtrl shall fulfil the following requirements for handling of incoming events of button presses.


</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B1B61">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_Display_Resource_Handling_for_HMICtrls</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_Display_Resource_Handling_for_HMICtrls</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT></TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B646C">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Management_of_menu_item</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Management_of_menu_item</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>Informative
This component manages the conditions to exit the menu 

Requirements:
Each time a display mode dedicated to menu views is granted (Referring to document: HMI resource coordination RT), the nil reference  timer shall be started from 0.

Each time the driver use any “Navigation in DID” buttons (Referring to “buttons” tab in document: HMI resource coordination RT), thenil reference  timer shall be restarted.

If the display mode dedicated to menu views is Released or Stacked, the timer shall be stopped.

Conditions for exiting the menu:
When any of the following conditions becomes true, this LDC shall ask for exiting the menu:
The ReturnToPageWhenIdleTime  timer has elapsed
The “Menu” button is pressed
The Vehicle Mode changes from pre-running or above, to below pre-running

When the conditions for exiting the menu are fulfilled:
- release display mode dedicated to menu views
- send “ExitMenuRequest” through the XXAppEvCmd. “XX” should be replaced by the name of the HMICtrl.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B7139">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_Fault_notification_system_initiated</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_Fault_notification_system_initiated</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>This Behavior Description is responisble for the presentation of all fault notifications in initiated by activated DTCs in the vehicle.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B18C6">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Failure_handling_for_soft_telltales_in_dynamic_cluster</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Failure_handling_for_soft_telltales_in_dynamic_cluster</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>In case of a dynamic cluster in the truck most of the physical telltales in the cluster are replaced by a soft telltale in the display area of the dynamic cluster. This requiement is about how to handle those soft tellatels in a failure situation.

The soft tellales shall not be lit when this component receivs Error or Not available by the signal representing whether the soft telltale shall be lit or not.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
