                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BD928">
                  <SHORT-NAME>CC_ACC_ASL_vehicle_messages</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>CC_ACC_ASL_vehicle_messages</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>Signals nil reference and nil reference shall trigger a Vehicle Message for some of their values. 

The following tables specifie theses values and the HMI IDs of the corresponding vehicle messages.

nil reference
Vehicle Message HMI ID
activation_failed_no_selection
601
CC_deactivation_warning
221
CC_deselected_error
222
CC_activation_failed_error
222
CC_activation_failed_low_speed
388
CC_activation_brake_pedal_check
389
CC_activation_stop_braking
390
ASL_deselected_error
223
ASL_deactivation_warning
223


nil reference
Vehicle Message HMI ID
ACC System shut off warning
391
ACC Not available, error
633
ACC Failed to activate, due to too low speed
393
ACC Not available, retarder requested
392

These vehicle messages shall be handled in the full control mode via signal  nil reference.
When signal nil reference changes to a value of the first table (1), or when signal nil reference changes to a value of the second table(1), the corresponding vehicle message shall be activated.
Once a vehicle message is active, it shall be deactivated if any of the following condition occurs:
signal nil reference changes to a value of the first table (1)
OR signal nil reference changes a value of the second table (1)
OR signal nil reference changes to 'cruise control enabled'
OR signal nil reference changes to On
OR signal nil reference changes to On
OR signal nil reference changes to On
(1) The signal shall change from x to y where xy and y is in the table.

If signal nil reference or nil reference is missing the corresponding vehicle messages shall not be activated.
If signal  nil reference is missing, replacement value 'cruise control disabled' shall be used in this requirement.
If signal nil reference is missing, replacement value Off shall be used in this requirement.
If signal nil reference is missing, replacement value Off shall be used in this requirement.
If signal nil reference is missing, replacement value Off shall be used in this requirement.

Notes:
Only one of these vehicle message can be active at a given time.
Once activated, a vehicle message will be deactivated after the time-out specified in the NPP table if none of the  deactivation condition listed above has occurred before.
The current vehicle message is deactivated if the condition to activate a new vehicle message is reached. The new vehicle message can be the same as the current one; in that case it will be reactivated for the complete time-out period, or until one of the deactivation condition occurs.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BD992">
                  <SHORT-NAME>CC_ACC_ASL_user_feedback_views_RT_HD_</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>CC_ACC_ASL_user_feedback_views_RT_HD_</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>For some of its values, signal nil reference shall trigger user feedback views containing dynamic data. 

The following table specifies the values that shall trigger a user feedback view and the corresponding view IDs and the signals that shall be used to present the dynamic data in the view.
