nil referencenil referencenil reference

When signal nil reference changes to a value of this table (1), the corresponding view shall be activated. 
Once activated the view shall be displayed until any of the following condition occurs:
signal nil reference has been set to no_request during nil reference
OR signal nil reference changes to a value of this table (1); in that case the new view shall immediately replace the current view
OR the CC is being disabled (signal nil reference changes from 'cruise control enabled' to a different value)
OR the CC is being deactivated (signal nil reference changes from On to a different value)
OR the ASL is being disabled (signal nil reference changes from On to a different value)
OR the ASL is being deactivated (signal nil reference changes from On to a different value)
The driver shall also have the possibility to remove the view while it is displayed
This shall be done using signal nil reference.

(1) The signal shall change from x to y where xy and y is in the table.

For notifications CC_preset1_stored, CC_preset2_stored, ACC_preset1_stored, ACC_preset2_stored, ASL_preset1_stored and ASL_preset2_stored, a sound request shall be requested through signal nil reference.

If signal nil reference is missing or indicates error or not available, then no_request shall be used as replacement value
If signal  nil reference is missing, replacement value 'cruise control disabled' shall be used in this requirement.
If signal nil reference is missing, replacement value Off shall be used in this requirement.
If signal nil reference is missing, replacement value Off shall be used in this requirement.
If signal nil reference is missing, replacement value Off shall be used in this requirement.

Dynamic data shall be refreshed while the view is visible.

The set or preset speed data (nil reference, nil reference, nil reference, nil reference, nil reference, nil reference) shall be presented either in km/h or in mph depending on the configuration (nil reference) and the speed unit selected by the driver, and shall be rounded to the nearest entire value before being displayed in the instrument cluster.

When the unit is mph, a conversion shall be done before rounding, using the following rate:
1 km/h = 0.6213711922222 mph

A view shall be disabled if a signal needed to elaborate its dynamic data is missing or indicates error or not available or is out of its operational range.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
