                  <SHORT-NAME>Liquid_Natural_Gas_Vehicle_Messages</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Liquid_Natural_Gas_Vehicle_Messages</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>Signals nil reference, nil reference shall trigger a Vehicle Message for some of their values. 

The following tables specify theses values and the HMI IDs of the corresponding vehicle messages.

nil reference
Vehicle Message HMI ID
LNG system warming up, Please Wait
787
LNG in Limping mode
791


nil reference
Vehicle Message HMI ID
LowFuelLevelWarning_ON
788

These vehicle messages shall be handled in the full control mode via signal  nil reference.
When signal nil reference changes to a value, the corresponding vehicle message shall be activated.
Once a vehicle message is active, it shall be deactivated if any of the following condition occurs: 


Vehicle message 787:  In VM Running shall be,  activated by nil reference signal status:LNG system warming up, Please Wait [1] and deactivated by signalstatus  LNG system ready [3]. 
Vehicle message 791:  In VM Running shall be activated and deactivated by nil reference signal status: LNG in Limping mode [2].
If nil reference signal is missing , Not available, Undefined or Error, no message shall be activ.

Vehicle message 788 :  In VM Running shall be activated  by nil reference signal status:LowFuelLevelWarning_ON[1] .and deactivated by LowFuelLevelWarning_OFF[0]
If  nil reference signal is missing , Not available, Undefined or Error, no message shall be activ


</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
