                  <SHORT-NAME>BB_access_to_brakes</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BB_access_to_brakes</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>IF nil reference = 1
AND (nil reference &lt;> 0 OR nil reference &lt;> 0 OR nil reference &lt;> 0 OR nil reference &lt;> 0 OR nil reference &lt;> 0)
AND nil reference = &quot;ON&quot;

THEN
{
(nil reference (BB Access to Brake) = On) signal shall be sent.
Note: This will trigger related viewflows, as described in DIDGUI_ctrl:
nil reference: the icon described in the document 26331-473, View 002 (BB_acces_to_brakes.pdf)
nil reference: a message and an icon shall be displayed in the construction page according to view BAB-H-001 (respectively BAB-B-001). Then the message shall be removed according to view BAB-H-002 (respectively BAB-B-002).
}

ELSE
{
(nil reference (BB Access to Brake) = Off) signal shall be sent.
}</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BE16C">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Remote_Full_Brakes</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Remote_Full_Brakes</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>IF nil reference = 1
AND nil reference = &quot;Active&quot;

THEN
{
(nil reference (Remote Full Brakes) = On) signal shall be sent.
Note: This will trigger related viewflows, as described in DIDGUI_ctrl:
nil reference: the icon described in the document 26331-473, View 004 (BB_acces_to_brakes.pdf)
nil reference: a message and an icon shall be displayed in the construction page according to view BAB-H-005. Then the message shall be removed according to view BAB-H-006.
}

ELSE
{
(nil reference (Remote Full Brakes) = Off) signal shall be sent.
}</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
