                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BD9F7">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_BatterySOC_SOH</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_BatterySOC_SOH</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The battery information display must include on the same bar-graph SOCnom &amp; SOH, so that the customer understands that the more the batteries are aged, the less they are able to be charged. The driver should not have access to more details (no value in %). The bar graph status must change step by step, especially between 100% and 80% SOH in order to avoid any claim with the customer. 
segments. 

Some examples: 

Example for SOH= 78% and SOCnom= 70% at +25°C: The batteries can be charged until 78%. If the driver stops the engine he will receive a warning saying: “battery charge recommended for long stop”


Example for SOH =60% and SOCnom = 55%, at +25°C. The batteries are aged and will soon lead to a failure; the driver receives an alert “battery maintenance” and will also see below the bar graph: “life on board limited”


Example for SOH =59% and SOCnom = 49% at +25°C. The batteries are aged and will soon lead to a failure, the driver already has a “battery maintenance” alert and receives also: “cranking not secured”


Note: The design of bargraph and alerts above are just examples. The alerts and their texts will be specified in BatterySOCAlert.
</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001BA7EC">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_BatterySOCAlert</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_BatterySOCAlert</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>BatterySOCAlert_rqst
A-pop up or similar shall be presented on SID or DID to alert the driver that the SOC level is low. Two levels of alerts are possible with different texts in the pop-up. The driver must acknowledge the pop-up.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
