                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B7959">
                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_MainMenu</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_MainMenu</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The nil reference is responsible for the main menu in the DID and for the navigation within this menu. Parts of the menu in the DID may be distributed among the different applications in the vehicle since they may be dynamically generated during runtime (e.g. MP3 lists, adress books etc). The DID Main Menu is also responsible for display settings, like brightness, colour etc. The DID Main Menu also includes features like password protection of menu items, including the possibility to change password. 

The menu structure shall be pre-defined and support all possible configurations of external devices on the entertainment network. The menu structure is still TBD. Menu entries addressing devices that are not present in the current configuration must not show up in the menus displayed. Functions that are not available due to current system situation (e.g. next track when no CD is present) shall be clearly distinguished from available function, e.g by a gray color. These functions shall not be possible to select.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
