                  <SHORT-NAME>BehaviorDescription_ASL_presentation</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>BehaviorDescription_ASL_presentation</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The Adjustable Speed Limiter functionality controls the engine injection in order to not overshoot  the vehicle speed target set by the driver. 
This function displays Adjustable Speed Limiter information on the Instrument Cluster. The following items shall be displayed:
The Adjustable Speed Limiter max speed selected by the driver.
The max speed unit selected by the driver.
A status icon indicating that the Adjustable Speed Limiter function is active. 
This function shall also be able to display visual effects in order to warn the driver in some special situations.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
