              <OPERATIONAL-SITUATIONS/>
              <REQUIREMENTS>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B4A55">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_Disabled_while_ACC_Failure</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ACC_Disabled_while_ACC_Failure</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall not be possible to activate or resume ACC while ACC function is in failure mode.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A7E55">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Brake_light_activation</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Brake_light_activation</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>If foundation brakes are applied due to ACC deceleration request the brake lights shall be activated within 200ms.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A570B">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Brakes_applied_information_usage</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Brakes_applied_information_usage</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>Systems which use “brakes applied” information (e.g. automatic gearbox) shall not only consider brake switch information for this purpose, but shall as well consider an information from the brake system (e.g. FoundationBrakeUsage) that brakes are applied, as they can be applied due to deceleration request by ACC.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A6151">
                  <SHORT-NAME>CC_Activation_while_ACC_Failure</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>CC_Activation_while_ACC_Failure</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to resume or activate CC, even if ACC is in failure mode.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A7E5C">
                  <SHORT-NAME>CC_Shut_Off_on_ACC_Failure_Occurence_while_ACC_Active</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>CC_Shut_Off_on_ACC_Failure_Occurence_while_ACC_Active</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>When ACC is active and the ACC function is switched off due to a failure, even the CC function shall switch off at the same time when the ACC function switches off (delay &lt; 100ms).</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC626">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Default_Timegap</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Default_Timegap</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC timegap shall while ignition is off be initialised with a pre-defined default timegap.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A7E63">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_Failure</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ACC_Failure</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to inform the driver that ACC is not available due to failure within 200ms after status has changed to failure. If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B49CF">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_Relinquished</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ACC_Relinquished</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The driver shall be informed when ACC is relinquished (has switched off) due to non driver initiated reasons within 200ms after change of status. If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B497C">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Adjust_Timegap</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Adjust_Timegap</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to adjust (increase or decrease) the timegap in (not more than) 5 steps in a configurable range.

NOTE: The TimeGap will internally inside the ACC be transformed to a time-gap in seconds.


</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B4A5C">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Brake_Capacity_Warning</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Brake_Capacity_Warning</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to present a Brake capacity warning to the driver. The warning shall be presented within 200ms after being issued. If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A6141">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Deselect_ACC</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Deselect_ACC</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to deactivate ACC separately from CC and just choose CC. If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A6149">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Distinction_between_ACC_and_CC</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Distinction_between_ACC_and_CC</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible for the driver to determine whether ACC or CC are active, to make it possible for the driver to see which of both functions is active. If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A7E7B">
                  <SHORT-NAME>PresentTimegap</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>PresentTimegap</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to present the selected timegap and changes in the selected timegap to the driver (changes of TG shall be displayed within 200ms after changing at the latest). If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575. 
NOTE: The timegap shall be displayed in a graphical way and not as figures (e.g. NOT 3s, but   TV _ _ _ SV) </TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A7E8B">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Target_Vehicle_Detected</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Target_Vehicle_Detected</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to inform the driver that ACC has detected and selected a Target Vehicle. The information must be displayed to the driver within 200ms after change of status (not detected / detected / not detected).  If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B4C12">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Target_Vehicle_Information</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Target_Vehicle_Information</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible to inform the driver of the following information dependent on the variant: 
1. The distance to the Target Vehicle (preferred)
2. The absolute velocity of the Target Vehicle.

If using HMI symbols, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A664D">
                  <SHORT-NAME>RoadCurvatureClass</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>RoadCurvatureClass</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC system shall be compliant to the definition of performance class III in ISO 15622. Thus the ACC system shall be capable of detecting objects in the path of the Subject Vehicle along any curve of radius 250 meters or greater and shall be fully operational as defined in ISO and following: The ACC system shall enable steady state vehicle following with the maximum time gap (4s) on straight roads and curves with a radius down to Rmin,III 250 m (class III). Therefore the system shall be capable to follow a forward vehicle with the steady state maximum time gap, if the forward vehicle cruises on a constant curve radius Rmin with a constant speed of app. 86 km/h.  The speed is derived from a max. lateral acceleration of 2,3 m/s2 at the radius 250m.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC63A">
                  <SHORT-NAME>TrafficEnvironment</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>TrafficEnvironment</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC function shall be designed for use on Highways and Rural Roads.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A6662">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Type_of_Objects</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Type_of_Objects</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC system shall be able to react on the following type of objects: 
Forward motor vehicles (travelling in same direction and path) and stopped motor vehicles (stationary in path) which have been detected as moving before. As motor vehicles motorcycles, cars, light trucks, goods vehicles, heavy trucks and other heavy vehicles are considered. 

The ACC system shall not react on bicyclist or stationary objects or on any type of vehicles in on-coming traffic. </TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC640">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Compatibility</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Compatibility</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC system shall be compliant to ISO 15622 (type 2b, performance class III), unless explicitly otherwise noted in other requirements.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A6653">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Deceleration_Limits_in_Owner_Manual</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Deceleration_Limits_in_Owner_Manual</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The deceleration capability of the ACC system shall be clearly stated in the vehicle owner’s manual. This is a requirement in accordance with ISO 15622.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC65A">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_mode_information</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ACC_mode_information</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible for the driver to see which ACC mode he/she has chosen.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC660">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_mode_selection</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ACC_mode_selection</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>It shall be possible for the driver to select between the ACC modes STANDARD and ECONOMY.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B4A07">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_mode_Standard_or_Economy</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ACC_mode_Standard_or_Economy</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>ACC shall have (at least) two different headway tuning parameter setups: The STANDARD mode and an ECONOMY mode.
Economic mode shall save fuel compared to standard mode.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A9CBA">
                  <SHORT-NAME>RollerBenchMode</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>RollerBenchMode</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC function shall be disabled (no acceleration or retardation requests) if the vehicle is in nil reference.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B4C22">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Interaction_with_Retarder</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Interaction_with_Retarder</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC system behaviour and performance shall not be negatively influenced by any driveline retarder setting.
  </TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001A7B80">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Jack_Knife_Effect_Avoidance</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Jack_Knife_Effect_Avoidance</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC system shall always use a vehicle control incl brake strategy to avoid safety critical situations like e.g. Jack Knife effects (e.g. if trailer has no ABS). This can be in particular the use of appropriate brake system (foundation brakes, auxiliary brakes) and the gradient of change of acceleration can be influenced.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC78B">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Observable_Behavior</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Observable_Behavior</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The following behaviour must be handled in a controlled manner by the E2E function. Requirements will be broken down to nil reference where faults shall be detected and each reported as a nil reference.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC62D">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Timegap_adjustment_symbols</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Timegap_adjustment_symbols</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>If using HMI symbols for timegap adjustments, it is recommended that they are conforming to corresponding ISO 2575.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B49B9">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Left_hand_and_right_hand_traffic_environment</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Left_hand_and_right_hand_traffic_environment</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC function shall work independently of left-hand or right-hand traffic environment. Thus ACC functionality will work in the same way for both  left-hand and right-hand drive applications.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC654">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Default_ACC_mode</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Default_ACC_mode</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>ACC STANDARD mode shall be default while ignition is off.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC667">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_economy_mode</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ACC_economy_mode</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC ECONOMY mode shall be tuned to achieve a fuel saving compared to the ACC STANDARD mode.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001AC796">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Time_gap_adjustment_while_ignition_is_off</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Time_gap_adjustment_while_ignition_is_off</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The ACC timegap shall not be adjustable while ignition is off.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000001B4C36">
                  <SHORT-NAME>Black_out_and_Convoy_mode</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>Black_out_and_Convoy_mode</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>If Black Out Mode or Convoy Mode is active then the ACC shall (within 500 ms) be in state ACC off.

This requirement says that the ACC system shall not try to control the vehicle speed and/or send warnings when the vehicle is set to black out mode or convoy mode. In this mode there shall be no sensor transmission or warning activations, it shall be shut off during &quot;black out and convoy mode&quot;.</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000005FCAE2">
                  <SHORT-NAME>TSRVehicleReqPlaceholder</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>TSRVehicleReqPlaceholder</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT></TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000007F9EAB">
                  <SHORT-NAME>ASL_SpeedLimitation</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>ASL_SpeedLimitation</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>ASL shall secure VehicleSpeed to be the minimum of selected speed limitation and RequestedSpeed </TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000008B61EF">
                  <SHORT-NAME>TestChart9</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>TestChart9</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT></TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000008B61F2">
                  <SHORT-NAME>TestChart10</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>TestChart10</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT></TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT UUID="x04000000008B61F5">
                  <SHORT-NAME>TestChart11</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME>TestChart11</NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT></TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT>
                  <SHORT-NAME>ACC_V1</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY></CATEGORY>
                  <NAME></NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>   If the speed is below the traffic sign speed and the lane is free the vehicle can accelerate at 1 m/s^2 until the speed reaches: driver set-speed or TSR max speed</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT>
                  <SHORT-NAME>TSR_V2</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY>Proposed</CATEGORY>
                  <NAME></NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>Vehicle speed shall not exceed limit of road signs when RSL is active</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT>
                  <SHORT-NAME>TSR_V3</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY>Proposed</CATEGORY>
                  <NAME></NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>The TSR shall work for the following output range: x = [0m, 100m], y = [-30m, 30m] z = [0m, 20m]; x = longitudinal, y = transverse, z = vertical</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
                <REQUIREMENT>
                  <SHORT-NAME>TSR_V4</SHORT-NAME>
                  <CATEGORY>Proposed</CATEGORY>
                  <NAME></NAME>
                  <OWNED-COMMENTS/>
                  <TEXT>TSR shall work for the following countries and speed sign types: SE, DK, SF, D, UK</TEXT>
                  <FORMALISM></FORMALISM>
                  <URL></URL>
                  <MODE-REFS/>
                </REQUIREMENT>
              </REQUIREMENTS>
              <REQUIREMENTS-RELATIONSHIP-GROUPS/>
              <REQUIREMENTS-HIERARCHYS/>
              <USE-CASES/>
              <REQUIREMENT-TYPES/>
            </REQUIREMENTS-MODEL>
